      "\\(\\dfrac{x}{y}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{y}{x}\\)",
      "\\(1\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "Take log: \\(2019\\ln x+2020\\ln y=4039\\ln(x+y)\\).\n\nDifferentiating:\n\n\\[\\frac{2019}{x}+\\frac{2020}{y}\\frac{dy}{dx}=\\frac{4039}{x+y}\\left(1+\\frac{dy}{dx}\\right)\\]\n\nSince \\(\\dfrac{x^{2019}y^{2020}}{(x+y)^{4039}}=1\\), the structure simplifies and \\(\\dfrac{dy}{dx}=\\dfrac{y}{x}\\).",
    "name": "Implicit Differentiation Power Law"
  },
  {
