      "\\(\\dfrac{-1}{\\sqrt{9-x^2}}\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "Let \\(x=3\\cos A\\). Then \\(\\dfrac{4x^3}{27}-x=4\\cos^3A-3\\cos A=\\cos3A\\) is incorrect; let me redo. Actually: \\(\\dfrac{4x^3}{27}-x\\) with \\(x/3=\\cos A\\): \\(4\\cos^3A-3\\cos A=\\cos3A\\).\n\n\\(y=\\cos^{-1}(\\cos3A)=3A=3\\cos^{-1}(x/3)\\)\n\n\\[\\frac{dy}{dx}=\\frac{-3}{\\sqrt{1-(x/3)^2}}\\cdot\\frac{1}{3}=\\frac{-3}{\\sqrt{9-x^2}}\\]",
    "name": "Derivative of Inverse Cosine Composite"
  },
  {
