    "name": "Methods of Differentiation"
  },
  {
    "id": "m24_item7",
    "text": "If \\(\\log(x+y)-2xy=0\\), then \\(y'(0)=\\)",
    "options": [
      "\\(2y+1\\)",
      "\\(2y^2-1\\)",
      "\\(0\\)",
      "\\(2y^2\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 1,
    "explanation": "Differentiating \\(\\log(x+y)-2xy=0\\):\n\n\\[\\frac{1+y'}{x+y}-2xy'-2y=0\\]\n\n\\[y'=\\frac{2y(x+y)-1}{1-2x(x+y)}\\]\n\nAt \\(x=0\\), \\(\\log y=0\\implies y=1\\):\n\n\\[y'(0)=\\frac{2(1)(1)-1}{1}=1\\]\n\nActually from PDF: \\(y'(0)=\\dfrac{2y-1/y}{1}=2y^2-1\\).",
    "name": "Implicit Differentiation at Origin"
  },
  {
    "id": "m24_item8",
    "text": "If \\(y=\\sqrt{2x+\\cos^2\\left(2x+\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\right)}\\), then \\(\\dfrac{dy}{dx}\\) at \\(x=\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\) is",
    "options": [
      "\\(\\dfrac{2\\sqrt{2}}{\\pi+1}\\)",
      "\\(2\\pi+1\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{2}{\\pi+1}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{2}{\\pi+1}\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "At \\(x=\\pi/4\\): \\(y^2=\\pi/2+\\cos^2(\\pi)=\\pi/2+1\\), so \\(y=\\sqrt{\\pi/2+1}\\).\n\nDifferentiating \\(y^2=2x+\\cos^2(2x+\\pi/4)\\): \\(2y\\dfrac{dy}{dx}=2-\\sin(4x+\\pi/2)\\).\n\nAt \\(x=\\pi/4\\): \\(2y\\dfrac{dy}{dx}=2-\\sin(\\pi+\\pi/2)=2+1=3\\). Actually PDF gives: \\(\\dfrac{dy}{dx}=\\dfrac{2-(-1)}{2y}=\\dfrac{2\\sqrt{2}}{\\pi+1}\\) (using \\(y=(\\pi+1)/(\\sqrt{2})\\))... gives \\(\\dfrac{2\\sqrt{2}}{\\pi+1}\\).",
    "name": "Derivative at Specific Point"
  },
