    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "\\(f(x)=\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}-\\sin^{-1}\\left(\\sin\\dfrac{1+x}{x}+x^x\\right)=\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}-\\dfrac{1+x}{x}-x^x\\) (near \\(x=1\\) where values are small).\n\nWait — simplify: \\(\\sin\\dfrac{1+x}{x}=\\sin(1+1/x)\\). Let me use the derivative directly:\n\n\\(f'(x)=\\dfrac{-1}{2}\\cdot\\dfrac{1}{\\sqrt{1+x}}+x^x(1+\\ln x)\\)... At \\(x=1\\): \\(f'(1)=-\\dfrac{1}{4}+1=\\dfrac{3}{4}\\).",
