    "explanation": "Let \\(c=\\cos(\\sin^{-1}a)\\). Then \\(\\dfrac{x^2-y^2}{x^2+y^2}=c\\).\n\nBy componendo-dividendo: \\(\\dfrac{y^2}{x^2}=\\dfrac{1-c}{1+c}\\), so \\(y^2=kx^2\\) (constant ratio).\n\nDifferentiating \\(2yy'=2kx\\) with \\(k=y^2/x^2\\):\n\n\\[y'=\\frac{kx}{y}=\\frac{y^2/x^2\\cdot x}{y}=\\frac{y}{x}\\]",
    "name": "Implicit Differentiation of Inverse Trig Relation"
  },
